    <note>Liu(2) Yi(2) [1202] His son, Dao(2) [20281], has a sacrifial prayer drafted by Liu(2) Yizhi [3594], which identifies Dao(2) as an Yizhi's elder lineage cousin, and Liu Yizhi's sacrificial prayer for Yi(2)'s nephew, Jue [20280], does likewise. Jue's patrilineal ancestors through his father, Dingguo [20279], Yi(2)'s cousin [probably not brother], to Dingguo's great grandfather, Wenkui [20277], have no shared members with the ancestors of Yizhi. Therefore, I am tracing both branches of the lineage to Liu(2) P [16632]. I am identifying Yi(2) as a nephew of Shu [1230]. Zhejiang TZ, 123.31a; Wuxing zhi, 17.7a-7b; Jiangxi TZ, 9.36a; XCB, 292.2a, 294.3b, 297.7a, 301.10a, 306.6a-6b, 324.1a, 342.6a; Guangdong TZ, 15.3b-4a; SHY:ZG, 66.17a-17b, 27a-27b. CBD, 5, 3893-4.</note>
